rComments: Though Professor Grimes is a lovely person, I unfortunately did not learn much from this course. It was rather boring and the lectures were very disorganized. The classes were not engaging. I wish the content was a bit more stimulating. I do feel bad posting this, but if you want a stimulating final year media course, I would take something else.
Tough grader and overloaded work giver. Lectures DONT MAKE SENSE AT ALL! ! !
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Like Chun Wei Choo, Sara Grimes is probably one of the most student centered prof. if you like 0 student feedback/participation take classes with Colin Furness. Sara's classes half lecture half participatory, and very fair grading I suppose, had to work very hard for what I received. she has a very nice wardrobe collection! informative lectures
Lecture contents are totally disorganized but we are tested on many elements which she didn't mention in lecture at all. Inefficient grading and always being tough on marking assignments and exams.
Assigns difficult material, but is an easy marker. Expects class discussion in a lecture of 50+ people, and lets the same four individuals take up all the air time.

Good experience. Classes mostly participatory discussions. She's funny and down to earth. Super approachable and will help you out if you need it. Doesn't keep you in class if you don't need to be. Covers materials well and adapts readings to class interests. Positive experience all around.
